The Mandera county government has commissioned a Sh200 million fire station, which will help in mitigating disasters under its rapid response plan.
The plan has seen Mandera acquire two modern fire engines and other assorted equipment, besides building a command centre.
Mandera Governor Ali Roba described the development as iconic and part of his legacy as he leaves office in 2022 after serving for two terms.



