Residents of Mandera town welcomed the project, and urged the county government to extend the same service to other towns.
“Previously residents would watch helplessly as their property went up in flames. We are proud today that we have an effective response team whose results we have seen in recent days,” said Ms Alphone Dahir.





Firefighters display some of their equipment.
Photo credit: Manase Otsialo | Nation Media Group


Managed fire outbreaks
The new fire brigade has managed to effectively contain several outbreaks in Mandera town, including a fire incident at Moi Girls' Secondary School.
Governor Roba applauded the fire brigade, promising to have more funds allocated for better equipment.
“Let us congratulate the team for a job well done. At Kamor Primary School, they contained a field fire and at Koromey farms, they have contained several wild bush fires,” he said.



