Records in Mandera Municipality indicate the county recorded 13 fire incidents in 2018, another 29 cases in 2019 and 155 cases in 2020.
The team consists of 28 trained firefighters.
To keep the fire brigade prepared, Governor Roba’s administration organises regular drills to keep the fire crew fit for assignments.
The Mandera Municipality fire station sits on a two-acre piece of land and is equipped with an underground water tank with a capacity of 100,000 litres.
Mr Roba said Mandera town has critical installations, including an airport, and a fast growing urban area all of which require emergency fire rescue teams to be always ready.
“We remain committed to building their capacity and investing in the expansion of this service throughout the county,” he said.
Train youth
He promised to ensure that the youth are sponsored to train in emergency rescue operations.
The governor ordered the county’s Ministry of Roads and Public Works to ensure that all building plans come with fire detection equipment as a preventive measure for fire disasters.
“I hereby direct the Ministry of Public Works to ensure all county government buildings are fitted with fire detection equipment going forward,” he said.



